	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>3d January 1866</date>.</p>
				<p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I send you the conclusion<lb/> of the Biography&#44; and must ask your kind<lb/> attention to the additions to the last<lb/> copy sent which I hope will be in<lb/> time. One is an addition to the list of books&#44;<lb/> the second is to come in as a note. I <lb/> have written them on a <sic>seperate</sic> sheet&#44;<lb/> finding too that the Biography has swelled<lb/> to larger proportions than I at first thought.<lb/>  I closed it with a few words words of dedication.<lb/> I think however they had better not<lb/> appear in the occident&#44; but on a <sic>seperate</sic><lb/> page following the title&#8212;now the title to be<lb/> finished yet&#44; I would say at the back<lb/> of that&#59; but I presume that cannot be<lb/> easily done&#44; &#38; the difference of expense<lb/> must be very trifling&#44; so the <sic>seperate</sic> page is</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>perhaps the best. Please let me know<lb/>  whether you have altered the grave error<lb/> to which I referred in my last and<lb/> which necessitates cancel pages. And<lb/> as you have all the copy now&#44; I would<lb/> like to learn from you at your<lb/> earliest possible convenience what<lb/> I am to pay for the &#8220;Extras&#8221;.  Further<lb/> as I have an idea of putting the<lb/> pamphlet in colored paper wrappers<lb/> with title&#44; please let me know what<lb/> this will cost extra ere I decide&#8212;<lb/> of course I mean the difference between<lb/> receiving the work <hi rend="underline">in sheets</hi>&#44; and<lb/> sewed in pamphlet form &#38; covers <add>&#63;</add><lb/> as mentioned.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It is not because the<lb/> pamphlet is <hi rend="underline">large</hi> that I have written<lb/> a dedication to <persName>Sir Moses</persName> but<lb/> he has been like a second</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>parent to our family&#44; and apart<lb/> from what he has done for <placeName>Israel</placeName><lb/> and his many other claims to esteem<lb/> I always think of him&#44; as I owe him<lb/> the highest gratitude. He was also<lb/> one of the best friends of my grandfather<lb/> <persName>Haham<add>&#63;</add> Meldola&#39;s</persName>.  When he goes&#44; who<lb/> is there to have his place among the<lb/> orthodoxy.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Sam Benjamin</persName> <add>&#63;</add> of this city<lb/> has lost his only son a fine young<lb/> man at <placeName>Nassau</placeName>&#8212; <persName>Wm Benjamin</persName><lb/> is going in a few weeks to <placeName>England</placeName><lb/> on business and I will then ask<lb/> him to speak about your accounts.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am still owing you a<lb/> small balance which I will send<lb/> with the amount for the pamphlet<lb/> Please make a bill for it&#44; adding<lb/> the sermon extras.</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am not in receipt of the <date>Jany</date><lb/> <sic>occident</sic> yet. We seldom get it before<lb/> the middle of the month. Why is this&#63;<lb/> I thought you published on the first&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Should the note on <add>&#63;</add><lb/> be not in time for the last copy sent<lb/> please add it to the copy now sent.<lb/> Its place would be at the beginning<lb/> of the copy thus &#8220;with the above list <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I must close&#44; as I have to see<lb/> a gentleman or contemplate application<lb/> to our legislature for an  Education<lb/> bill versus the Catholics &#8212; Please let<lb/> me hear from you soon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">I remain yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
				<p>I have marked<lb/> the dedication D that<lb/> it may not be mixed with<lb/> the other copy. &#45; When  all is printed I<lb/> shall have a few errata to send you.</p>
		</body>
